-steel-125122401124_1.html","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2025-12-24T20:37:38","source":"Business Standard"},{"id":"420907","title":"Nuvama cuts Jindal Steel's price target by 9.7% to ₹1,264, still implying a 24.8% upside.\nJSPL's EBITDA CAGR forecast is 28% for FY25-28, despite near-term steel price, cost challenges.","summary":"Nuvama cuts Jindal Steel's price target by 9.7% to ₹1,264, still implying a 24.8% upside.\nJSPL's EBITDA CAGR forecast is 28% for FY25-28, despite near-term steel price, cost challenges.","url":"https://www.cnbctv18.com/market/jspl-share-price-nuvama-cuts-target-maintains-buy-upside-key-triggers-capacity-19801385.htm","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2025-12-24T13:33:19","source":"CNBC TV 18"},{"id":"420827","title":"IndiGo, Jindal Steel, and Zydus Lifesciences topped five-year December returns, while Kirloskar Brothers and Thomas Cook lagged.\nNifty Midcap 100 and Smallcap 100 outperformed Nifty 50 in December; analysts forecast FY26-27 earnings growth of 10-16% YoY.","summary":"IndiGo, Jindal Steel, and Zydus Lifesciences topped five-year December returns, while Kirloskar Brothers and Thomas Cook lagged.\nNifty Midcap 100 and Smallcap 100 outperformed Nifty 50 in December; analysts forecast FY26-27 earnings growth of 10-16% YoY.","url":"https://www.ndtvprofit.com/markets/december-scorecard-indigo-to-thomas-cook-stocks-that-clocked-best-worst-five-year-returns","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2025-12-24T12:54:08","source":"NDTV Profit"}]}]